entries.femaleVariant: And the occasion would be...?
[Drink] Count me in.
I'll take a swig.
Over here, V! Take a seat! We have this little ritual we engage in.
[Sit] What's this ritual?
What's this ritual about?
A few cold ones ahead of a raid.
Mind if I join you?
Mind if join ya? Doubt I even remember what it's like not to hear my mind churnin' away.
If you like.
Twelve bottles shattered in fifteen seconds. Full focus – tha'ss your only chance at doin' it. I'm doubtful you'll pull it off.
Begin!
The line, do you see the line?
Stop!
Piss poor. This doe'n't bode well for tomorrow, kid.
It'll do. But I swear I heard your thoughts rumblin' on.
That'll do almost, kid. But practice makes perfect.
Not bad. You coulda done better, but you coulda done worse.
Twelve bottles of beer off the wall. It like in those westerns o' yore – "I got nothin' left to teach ya."
Christ! What kind of machinery have you got in there? You should be givin' me lessons.
Never drink ahead of a mission.
Thanks. Rather keep a clear head, though.
entries.maleVariant: Thanks, rather keep a clear head, though.

entries.femaleVariant: I can't say I get it, but I respect it.
Ah, that kind.
V! Hey, how's things? Is everything going all right?
It's goin'. Yourself?
You all right?
The end times.
You could say that.
[Take revolver] Thanks.
Your gun, can't accept it.
Thanks, Cass, but... I think you should keep it. Suits you more.
entries.maleVariant: Thanks, Cass, but I think you should keep it. Suits you more.

entries.femaleVariant: Thanks, Cass.
Hm, maybe you're right.
Essentially. Take what you want.
You, uh… mad at me?
I once found a dead magpie under the hood of my car.
It had been a cold night. The magpie, looking for warmth, had found the engine. It couldn't get out next morning, got cooked alive.
I still remember the smell – charred feathers, misery, death.
The moment I met you, that vision appeared before my eyes. Today, I understand why.
But your future is not etched in stone, V – remember that.
Worthy gesture. Dramatic, even.
Actually, pragmatic. I'm giving away my stock to you so you survive tomorrow's mad hell and come back to me.
Yesss. Do you know what I realized today? That I'm one lucky son of an Irish gun.
Heh, that so?
Don't look at me that way – I'm clean. Look, there was the mine first, then that whole mess with the Wraiths…
But I'm here now. And you know what else? I'm not going anywhere.
I'll start countin' as soon as you step on that line.
One more time, now.
Let's find out.
Are you that confident? Well, I'll bet my revolver you can't do it.
"The trick is to hear silence in your mind at the bang." Learned somethin' after all.
You earned it.
Where's Mitch?
Where's Mitch?
To tomorrow.
Well, well, not bad.
What was it someone said, then...? Tsk, shit, can't remember who. Someone said, "When we finish 'em all, the Aldecaldos' luck will run out."
Aa, superstitious bullcrap is your hobby.
He was here just a second ago.
He said the panzer needed some fine-tuning.
That basilisk's seen better days. If I know Mitch, he be up to his elbows in grease till the crack of dawn.
We all have our own rituals.
Next time.
To goddam safe returns.
No, no. C major, then G.
'Kay,' kay, hold on!
Heh, I stink at this.
Know this number?
You having a sale?
What're you playin'?
What're you playin'?
Benedict?
You all right?
What's this? Yard sale of some sort?
It's Benedict, right?
Aim to prep for tomorrow?
Wait.
I feel I need to make one thing clear.
Dakota told me to sit tight for a while longer. Militech's still sniffin', just have to wait it out. Startin' to get itchy hands though, y'know?
But this isn't your average brew. It's one of the last bottles from our very first run. We kept a few crates, for good luck.
I'm just worried about that wall. How the hell are we gonna get over it?
Do you fellas really think we'll find anything of value there?
We gonna start worrying about that after tomorrow.
But once we're down south, you know where we could go? Bertie's.
You talking about that beat up old diner down by El Cajon?
What're you callin' beat up? They have the best spare ribs I ever had.
Teddy's right. You haven't tasted nothin', heathen woman.
It seldom happens, but they both seemed to agree on that point.
I'm going to buy myself a vintage RV.
Aheh, old age is hittin' hard, huh?
Haha.
Ah, screw you all.
Glad to hear it, Tanner. Lemme know if you need anything.
entries.maleVariant: Glad to hear it, Tanner. Let me know if you need anything.

entries.femaleVariant: Hmm?
You've done a lot for this clan. And for me, more than... anyone ever has. But the family comes first.
Saul…
Let me finish.
I also know there's just one thing that could break it up at this point. If Panam and me… if we went our separate ways.
The Aldecaldos would not survive that split were it to occur again. Do you understand what I'm trying to tell you?
You're helping 'cause you got no choice. Want the clan to think you and Panam are actin' as one. In other words, you're playin' politics.
entries.maleVariant: You're helpin' 'cause you got no choice. Want the clan to think you and Panam are actin' as one. In other words, you're playin' politics.

entries.femaleVariant: You're usin' me. The clan'll grab spoils from Mikoshi, while you do Panam a favor by helpin' me out. Hm, not bad, Saul.
entries.maleVariant: Now you're usin' me. The clan'll grab spoils from Mikoshi, while you do Panam a favor by helpin' me out. Not bad, Saul.

entries.femaleVariant: Wonder if Panam feels the same.
It isn't that simple.
V, I'll send these people to their deaths tomorrow. So I have to know I'm not doing it just for you, me or Panam.
But for the good of the clan. I get it.
You'll understand eventually. That jacket wasn't for nothing.
Helpin' me 'cause you don’t got no choice.
Usin' me to strengthen your position...
Wonder if Panam feels the same.
We good – you and me?
Take care, Saul.
Heh, says the brother who's hand is all shaky when he pops one open.
Now that's what we should drink to.
To Saul and Panam. Because if they don't kiss 'n' make up, everything's liable to go tits up.
Bob – you just always the optimist, ain't you.
Buried the hatchet. Saw it myself.
You really think they're at loggerheads?
Let's not talk about them. Wanna hear about you.
Think it's really that bad between 'em?
entries.maleVariant: You think it's really that bad between 'em?

entries.femaleVariant: Talked to them. They've buried the hatchet.
Had it up to here with the Panam versus Saul debate.
"Buried the hatchet"? Well, I'm really glad they've come to agree on sending us on a suicide mission.
Be cool, now, Bobby.
It's nothin' personal, V. I'm just sayin' how things are.
The truth is we need cash. And fast.
Amen.
This Mikoshi's a personal thing to you. But Saul, he sees an opportunity for the clan.
If anyone of the family is still left standin' tomorrow.
Sorry. It's all my fault.
Aldecaldos'll survive. I'll make sure of it.
Have faith in Saul.
Put your trust in Panam.
This is all my fault – I'm exposing the entire family to danger. I'm sorry.
entries.maleVariant: This is all my fault – I'm exposin' the entire family to danger. I'm sorry.

entries.femaleVariant: You've got nothin' to be sorry about.
The situation is fixin' to be a doozy, sure. But if the Aldecaldos are to rise from the ashes, it'll be thanks to you. And thanks to this raid.
Huh. For once I agree with him.
Can promise you one thing. Aldecaldos will survive. Make sure of it myself.
Easy on the promises, V.
But you're right. This clan has a chance to rise from the ashes.
I'm of the same mind. If we come back from Mikoshi, if this crazy-ass plan works – it'll be a fresh start for the Aldecaldos, I say.
Mhm. This feels like the part where Bobby says "IF."
Hey, now. I'm no defeatist, don't call me that.
Might wanna give Saul a fair chance here. Planned everything as best he could.
He should start planning his own retirement.
Would you wanna take his place?
Heh, not in a thousand years.
So I thought. Let's focus on tomorrow. We can talk politics once the dust's settled.
Amen.
Think Panam knows exactly what she's doin'.
But does she know what she wants? Useful if she wants to take the clan wheel.
Cool your heels, friend. No one's takin' over anything just yet.
We need to focus on tomorrow, brothers. Let's all get back in one piece – then we talk clan politics.
Best be goin'. See you tomorrow.
All right, best be goin'. See you tomorrow.
Join the club, child.
How're things goin' with you guys?
Not much to say. All seems set for tomorrow.
We still waitin' on some intelligence from the drone. Should know more come morning.
Apart from that, we're keepin' our toes crossed we don't get fucked tomorrow. Pardon my French.
Think we'll get it done tomorrow?
Everything ready?
Think we'll pull through tomorrow?
Everything prepped 'head of tomorrow?
I know these people. Some better than myself.
The focus of mind, sense of purpose, calm before the storm. They'll give it their all.
Huh, bet they will.
No worries. Everything's under control.
Good.
G'night, Saul.
You don't even believe that. You think I'd put the clan at peril for my own gain? What for?
Not the kind of guy to willingly surrender power.
entries.maleVariant: You're not the kind of guy to willingly surrender power.

entries.femaleVariant: And if all is lost tomorrow, who will I govern? Dust and ghosts?
You're wrong, V. This isn't about power. That jacket wasn't for nothing, V. You'll understand soon enough what it's like to be part of a whole.
You all think Panam and I are facing off, there's a... wall between us.
Isn't there?
Quite the contrary, V. Panam cares about this clan as much as I do.
Granted, we don't see all things the same way, but oddly enough, the family stands to benefit from that. I've seen it, and soon, you will, too.
How about us, Saul? We good?
Hope so. Take care, Saul. G'night.
entries.maleVariant: Hope so. Take care, Saul. Goodnight.

entries.femaleVariant: It's an important day tomorrow. Get some rest.
Goodnight.
Best not fuck with Dakota – that's good advice. And... look out for yourself.
entries.maleVariant: Best not to fuck with Dakota – that's good advice. And look out for yourself.

entries.femaleVariant: Let this be a reminder to ya.
Break a leg tomorrow.
Oh, I'll break more than that, kid.
Fine shootin', kid.
V, you must know where they stand. Do you?
You mad at me?
Uhh, OK... Sorry I even brought it up.
Samurai – know any of their songs?
Hey. Know any... Samurai songs?
On a night like this, I'm not thinkin' about anarchy. It's all about unity, sister.
entries.maleVariant: On a night like this, I'm not thinking about anarchy. It's all about unity, brother.

entries.femaleVariant: Revolver, empty bottles, middle o' nowhere – perfect.
"The trick is to hear silence in your mind at the bang."
I heard that a long time ago, 'round about when I was your age. I remember it to this day.
I’m expecting bangs in good numbers tomorrow, so I'm trying to remind myself of that silence.
Hmph. I'm a believer in old ways and legacy tech. I can't tell ya why, but I don't quite trust chrome.
How're things, Jake? All good?
Great, I'd say. The kidney's taken just like a new oil filter.
How goes, Bruce?
Hey, how ya been, Bruce? Sprouted your first shy roots yet?
Hey, V. Got a worn-out truth for you – camps aren't all alike. Feel at home here. I mean, like…
It's possible I'll make this my home? Dakota says I got valuable knowledge, like, safe passages south, areas to avoid… I dunno, but… feels good.
Glad to hear it. Good place for you, this.
entries.maleVariant: Glad to hear it. It's a good place for you, this.

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, hope it will be. Thanks again, V.
I need me some ammunition. Three or four packs' worth. Do you got any left?
I might have. You have to look around.
So maybe I'll take two more forty-fives, seein' as Dakota seems to be feeling generous today.
You have my thanks, V.
A life, a home
Years, lone roads
Ooo-oo, but the fire flamed high, boy's heart howling 'bout a life busted
With that fire raging hot, he kept on gunning for vengeance
In cinders scattered, glowing
Set this boy to roam
In his heart a fire unseen
Raging, growing
Busy streets a shadow
Crowds a bygone drone
And the starlight high above
Now his hearthstone
Then a badge with a grudge, picked a fight, oh, this boy got dusted
And the badge's slug doused the fire, made this boy a legend…
How you feeling?
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Drink]
Prepping for tomorrow?
Revolver, empty bottles – definitely your style.
